er cluster-centric\ndistances are more puffed-up, probably attributed to tidal interactions.\nFinally, the intermediate-redshift cluster UDGs are more flattened, which\nplausibly suggests a `disky' origin for high-redshift, initial UDGs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 23 Jul 2019 18:00:21 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 26 Jul 2019 02:17:01 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 22 Jun 2020 19:51:25 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 20 Jul 2020 21:50:15 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Tue, 28 Jul 2020 02:26:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-08-26"}
